1 C. High dosage tutors employed or contracted by public school
2 districts participating in the Oklahoma High Dosage Tutoring Program
3 shall be awarded bonuses in the following amounts:
4 1. One Thousand Six Hundred Dollars ($1,600.00) for each cohort
5 educated by a high dosage tutor per semester; and
6 2. One Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00) for each academic grade
7 level increase in English language arts or mathematics that each
8 student within a cohort experiences within one academic year.
9 D. If a high dosage tutor fails to achieve one-half grade level
10 of growth in students within a cohort within the first year of
11 participating in the program, he or she shall have one year of
12 probation as a participant in the program. If the high dosage tutor
13 fails to achieve one-half grade level of growth within a cohort
14 while on probation, he or she shall lose eligibility to participate
15 in the program.
16 E. The State Board of Education may promulgate rules to
17 implement the provisions of this section.
18 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
19 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-180.1 of Title 70, unless
20 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
21 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
22 for the State Department of Education to be designated the “High
23 Dosage Tutoring Revolving Fund”. The fund shall be a continuing
24 fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall consist of
